---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>🚀 Bruno Zub</h1>
			<p>
				<strong>IT Support Specialist & Junior Systems Administrator</strong>
			</p>
			<p>
				I'm transitioning from a career in video editing into IT and Systems Administration. 
				Over the last two years, I've built a production-grade homelab from the ground up, teaching myself virtualization, networking, containerization, and automation.
			</p>
			
			<h2>🛠️ Tech Stack</h2>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Infrastructure & Virtualization:</strong> Proxmox VE, Linux (Debian/Ubuntu), Windows Server, LXC</li>
				<li><strong>Containerization:</strong> Docker, Docker Compose, Portainer</li>
				<li><strong>Networking & Security:</strong> Tailscale (Zero Trust), Nginx, Cloudflare Tunnels, AdGuard Home (DNS Sinkholing), TCP/IP, DHCP</li>
				<li><strong>Storage:</strong> ZFS, SMB/NFS Shares</li>
				<li><strong>IT Operations:</strong> Active Directory, Nextcloud, Vaultwarden, RDP, SSH, VNC</li>
				<li><strong>Scripting & Hardware:</strong> Python, ESP32/Pi Pico, Desktop/Server Component Diagnostics & Assembly</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>💻 Infrastructure Projects</h2>
			<div class="projects">
				<h3>1. Hardware-Accelerated Container Environment</h3>
				<p>Architected a Proxmox-based home datacenter to run multiple isolated Linux (LXC) containers while sharing a single physical GPU through complex UID/GID mapping. This allowed for hardware-accelerated media transcoding and data processing without compromising container security perimeters.</p>
				<p><em>Tech: Proxmox VE, LXC, Debian CLI, GPU Passthrough, Privilege Management.</em></p>

				<h3>2. Hybrid-Cloud Reverse Proxy & Monitoring</h3>
				<p>Designed a hybrid network using a cloud VPS as a secure reverse proxy to route encrypted traffic to my on-premise homelab. Implemented Uptime Kuma to monitor 20+ active internal services with automated downtime alerting via webhooks.</p>
				<p><em>Tech: Cloud VPS, Nginx, Cloudflare Tunnels, Uptime Kuma, Zero-Trust Networking.</em></p>

				<h3>3. Self-Hosted Enterprise Infrastructure</h3>
				<p>Deployed a resilient, containerized suite of self-hosted enterprise services. This includes a ZFS-backed network storage solution for automated backups, network-wide DNS filtering, and node-based workflow automation to streamline server maintenance.</p>
				<p><em>Tech: Docker Compose, ZFS, SMB, Nextcloud, n8n, AdGuard Home.</em></p>
			</div>

			<p>
				<em>Note: Detailed documentation and architecture write-ups for these projects are available in my <a href="/blog">Blog</a> section.</em>
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
